    "Extended Summary": {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The font properties are the six properties described in the "
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "W3C Cascading Style Sheet, Level 1"
                }
              ],
              "title": "",
              "type": "link",
              "url": "http://www.w3.org/TR/1998/REC-CSS2-19980512/"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " font specification and "
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "math_fontfamily"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " for math fonts:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "family: A list of font names in decreasing order of priority.   The items may include a generic font family name, either 'sans-serif',   'serif', 'cursive', 'fantasy', or 'monospace'.  In that case, the actual   font to be used will be looked up from the associated rcParam during the   search process in "
                    },
                    {
                      "anchor": null,
                      "exists": true,
                      "kind": "module",
                      "reference": {
                        "kind": "module",
                        "module": "matplotlib",
                        "path": "matplotlib.font_manager:FontManager.findfont",
                        "type": "RefInfo",
                        "version": "3.6.2"
                      },
                      "type": "Link",
                      "value": ".findfont"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": ". Default: "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "font.family"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "style: Either 'normal', 'italic' or 'oblique'.   Default: "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "font.style"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "variant: Either 'normal' or 'small-caps'.   Default: "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "font.variant"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "stretch: A numeric value in the range 0-1000 or one of   'ultra-condensed', 'extra-condensed', 'condensed',   'semi-condensed', 'normal', 'semi-expanded', 'expanded',   'extra-expanded' or 'ultra-expanded'. Default: "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "font.stretch"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "weight: A numeric value in the range 0-1000 or one of   'ultralight', 'light', 'normal', 'regular', 'book', 'medium',   'roman', 'semibold', 'demibold', 'demi', 'bold', 'heavy',   'extra bold', 'black'. Default: "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "font.weight"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "size: Either an relative value of 'xx-small', 'x-small',   'small', 'medium', 'large', 'x-large', 'xx-large' or an   absolute font size, e.g., 10. Default: "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "font.size"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "math_fontfamily: The family of fonts used to render math text.   Supported values are: 'dejavusans', 'dejavuserif', 'cm',   'stix', 'stixsans' and 'custom'. Default: "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "mathtext.fontset"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            }
          ],
          "ordered": false,
          "spread": false,
          "start": 1,
          "type": "list"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Alternatively, a font may be specified using the absolute path to a font file, by using the "
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "fname"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " kwarg.  However, in this case, it is typically simpler to just pass the path (as a "
            },
            {
              "anchor": null,
              "exists": true,
              "kind": "module",
              "reference": {
                "kind": "api",
                "module": "pathlib",
                "path": "pathlib:Path",
                "type": "RefInfo",
                "version": "*"
              },
              "type": "Link",
              "value": "pathlib.Path"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ", not a "
            },
            {
              "domain": null,
              "role": null,
              "type": "Directive",
              "value": "str"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ") to the "
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "font"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " kwarg of the "
            },
            {
              "domain": null,
              "role": null,
              "type": "Directive",
              "value": ".Text"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " object."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The preferred usage of font sizes is to use the relative values, e.g.,  'large', instead of absolute font sizes, e.g., 12.  This approach allows all text sizes to be made larger or smaller based on the font manager's default font size."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "This class will also accept a "
            },
            {
              "domain": null,
              "role": null,
              "type": "Directive",
              "value": "fontconfig_"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " "
            },
            {
              "domain": null,
              "role": null,
              "type": "Directive",
              "value": "pattern_"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ", if it is the only argument provided.  This support does not depend on fontconfig; we are merely borrowing its pattern syntax for use here."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "placeholder": "target",
          "type": "Unimplemented",
          "value": ".. _fontconfig: https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/fontconfig/"
        },
        {
          "placeholder": "target",
          "type": "Unimplemented",
          "value": ".. _pattern:\n   https://www.freedesktop.org/software/fontconfig/fontconfig-user.html"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Note that Matplotlib's internal font manager and fontconfig use a different algorithm to lookup fonts, so the results of the same pattern may be different in Matplotlib than in other applications that use fontconfig."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
